Package ca.ualberta.cmput301w15t13.Models

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ExpenseClaim
    This is the Expense Claim interface It provides a minimum shared functionality for both claims and expenses It should be used to define the minimal functionality of an expenseClaim and it's constituent expenseItems Classes it works with: Claim, ExpenseItem
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Claim
    Class for claim.
    ClaimCurrencies
    This class holds a total of all the currencies in a claim It is used to keep track of the currency totals for each claim such that it can be displayed from a high level point of view It should be used as a container class To keep track of totals in predefined categories, and attached to a Claim object
    ClaimList
    A wrapper class for ArrayList with standard ArrayList methods.
    ClaimStatus
    This class is used to model the status of an expense claim.
    Currency
    Currency class is used to enumerate over all given currencies (as in the description).
    ExpenseItem
    Expense item class models the functionality of an expense Claim.
    ExpenseItemList
    This class is a container for individual expense items.
    Receipt
    This class is the model containing a user-taken photograph, ideally of a receipt.
    Tag
    This class models a Tag object.
    TravelItinerary
    This class represents a place the user wants to visit.
    TravelItineraryList
    This class is a model class for TravelItineraries.
